< text>
So, the 9v for my pickups was heating up. I took off the back cover and saw a tangled mess. I took it to Napa Music Supply and asked them to fix it. I paid $55 and they said they would try to put some kind of bracket to hold the battery. I
tested it at the shop and all seemed fine. Later I started noticing my tone knob had a bad connection and was cutting in and out. I took it apart and to my surprise... I found a $55 master piece!!! They took apart only 1 solder that was going from 1 wire to 4 wires... It still looks like garbage, still has bad connections and excessive solder... At to top it off... My 9v bracket is a piece of tissue wrapped around the battery and held on with a rubber band!<//text>

Really nice place to camp at, directly at the lake, with beach access
Beware though! Even though it's by the lake, right now it's pretty much overrun by bears each night because of its close proximity to the beach (leftovers at the parking...) and people leaving food at the tables at night / sending invites to the bears with smelly barbeques

<rate>4< /rate>< text>
Verizon has pretty good 4G reception here. Att straight talk/ NET10 have spotty reception. ..sometimes 2 bars 4H, sometimes no signal. You have to move around even within your campsite. The beach has consistent 4G for all carriers mentioned above. I stayed at camp site 34 and my straight talk hotspot (moxie) always had good 4G signal in this camp site and at beach . Screenshots are of NET10 /att signal at beach, at campsite 34 and an IPhone with Verizon at site 34. Fat bear here will harass campers that don't clean up their campsites and are cooking things like burgers. Bring your vegetarian meals instead. Don't count on hosts to take care of bear problems. Thumbs up me if helpful. :)</text>

<name>DeeDee White<//name><Date>1563567764846< /Date><rating>5</rating>< review>
This was our second year tent camping at Meeks Bay. We absolutely love this place. The staff is so wonderful and kind. The bathrooms are clean, campgrounds are clean, the general store has an AWESOME beer  selection, and the location is perfect.

Some other reviews mention being near the road, yes it is close to the road but it is not as close as some of the others near South lake. And the wall muffled the traffic noise. We stay at the first tent site against the road and it is not noticeable at all.

We are looking forward to next year! ‚ò∫Ô∏è<//review>

< username>
Leticia Andreas<//username>
< Date>
1529009553514< /Date>
<rating>4< /rating>< Review>
Campground is super clean and has great hosts - especially Michelle and Ricky! They are fabulous! Most people will love this campground. PROS: you can walk to the beach at the lake; lots of trees; decent sized sites; close to great hiking (one great trail is nearly right across the road); barely to no signal on your cell (a plus IMO). CONS: right at road, you always hear the traffic, and campground is in the road bend, so no matter where you camp you cannot escape traffic noise; fairly busy even though I was there during the week, and people had their music blasting; you will most likely not have a signal on your cell should you need it. I personally will not go back to Lake Tahoe area for camping ever, I'm more of an Eastern Sierra kind of girl. But like I said, most campers will probably love Meeks Bay campground and enjoy their stay very much.< /Review>

< Text>
Great beer selection in a large, inviting space with a lounging area, a children's play area, and outdoor seating which is dog friendly. The staff are very friendly, knowledgeable about the beer, and approachable.
In addition to the bar snacks and farm-direct fruit, there are rotating food vendors on the patio. There's lots of bike parking inside.

<resp>None< /resp><name>Madison Chaeli<//name>< Text>
When I first found Autism Therapy Career College, I thought it was too good to be true. I had been pursuing my RBT licensure without the guidance of an employer and supervisor. I reached the stage of the process where I needed a BCBA to approve my background check and to conduct the competency assessment. Not only did ATCC assure me that they would conduct a background check and attest to its completion, that they would conduct the competency assessment (with no need for a client), but also that they would sign the compassionate exception attestation (due to COVID-19) and would walk me through the RBT application to the BACB and it would be complete in the same session as the competency assessment. ATCC is incredibly communicative, invaluably helpful, and well worth every penny!<//Text>

< text>
So I wanted  a tattoo and started looking on Yelp at different places. I really liked the images they were showing. Very detailed and the shading was on point. My tattoo artist was very patient and thorough with my consultation.
